body:
### Description

During a single move operation, I start to get alternating touch co-ordinates like this:

    pt={X=156.8584, Y=207.1211}
    pt={X=170.8299, Y=225.1194}
    pt={X=157.8608, Y=208.1281}
    pt={X=170.8504, Y=226.1232}
    pt={X=157.8608, Y=209.132}
    pt={X=171.8323, Y=227.1271}
    pt={X=157.8435, Y=210.1358}
    pt={X=171.8323, Y=228.1309}
    pt={X=156.8616, Y=210.1185}
    pt={X=170.8299, Y=229.1521}
    pt={X=155.8592, Y=210.139}
    pt={X=170.8472, Y=230.1355}
    pt={X=154.8396, Y=210.1216}
    pt={X=170.8267, Y=231.1566}

This is unfiltered, as it comes in via `SKTouchEventArgs`. It visibly alternates between two, parallel moving values.

The strange thing is that nearly two years ago, in a completely unrelated theme (but, obviously, calling the same underlying platform services as you do), I already saw some very similar behavior: https://forums.xamarin.com/discussion/74168/full-screen-image-viewer-with-pinch-to-zoom-pan-to-move-tap-to-show-captions-for-xamarin-forms It's mentioned in the accepted answer, it was observed in scaling back then but the mechanism was the same.

I tried `IgnorePixelScaling` but it isn't any different. The actual values differ, the jumping around is still there. This was logical, after all.

### Basic Information

- Version with issue:  1.60.3
- Platform Target Frameworks:
  - Android: ???
  - UWP: 16299
